It’s part of a change to its content policy, the company says. A Google spokesperson told Reuters, developers only need to move their shopping cart option outside the app to comply. The tech firm said it’s working with many of them to answer technical questions and help them bring in the changes without disrupting customers. Existing apps have 30 days post-launch to obey. Canada became the first industrialized nation to legalize recreational cannabis back in October. Many other countries around the world are just approving medical marijuana. Wednesday’s news was hardly celebrated by those in the business. --Reuters--